## <a id="reqs"></a>Requirements

<%= vars.product_short %> requires the following:

* **<%= vars.product_short %> CLI:** For information about installing the <%= vars.product_short %> CLI, see
[Install the <%= vars.product_short %> CLI](./installing.html#ksm) .
* **<%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %> Deployment:** A running <%= vars.app_runtime_abbr %> deployment with runtime CredHub enabled that is installed on the
same foundation as <%= vars.product_short %>.
For instructions about enabling CredHub, see [Securing Services Instance Credentials with Runtime CredHub](https://docs.pivotal.io/pivotalcf/2-6/opsguide/secure-si-creds.html).
* **Kubernetes Cluster:** A running Kubernetes cluster. <%= vars.product_short %> supports <%= vars.k8s_runtime_full %> clusters. For information
about <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %>, see [<%= vars.k8s_runtime_full %>](https://docs.pivotal.io/pks/index.html).
* **<%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> CLI (optional):** If you use an <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> cluster, you must install
the <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> CLI. For information about installing the <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> CLI,
  see [Installing the <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> CLI](https://docs.pivotal.io/pks/installing-pks-cli.html).
* **Private Container Registry (optional):** You need this to manage container images
in air-gapped environments.
  VMware recommends using a private container registry in production deployments.
  You can use a private container registry such as
  [Harbor](https://network.pivotal.io/products/harbor-container-registry).
* **Helm 3 CLI (optional):** For information about installing the Helm CLI,
see the [Helm documentation](https://helm.sh/docs/intro/).
* **Docker CLI (optional):** For information about installing Docker, see [Docker](https://www.docker.com/).

## <a id="limitations"></a>Limitations

Dedicated service instances created by <%= vars.product_short %> provision
an IaaS load balancer for ingress into each service instance.
You cannot use ClusterIP for ingress.

